00:57:56.022 --> 00:57:59.402
But we also wanted to ask: What then is happening in the context of the primary

990
00:57:59.422 --> 00:58:02.442
lung? If we know that innervation is so important in the brain, which may make

991
00:58:02.542 --> 00:58:04.862
sense, what's going on in the context of the lung?

992
00:58:05.362 --> 00:58:09.302
We know that innervation is particularly important for homeostasis

993
00:58:09.362 --> 00:58:12.902
and regeneration in multiple different organs within the body.

994
00:58:13.582 --> 00:58:17.542
And using our genetic models then, we asked, how does innervation

995
00:58:17.602 --> 00:58:19.142
look in these small cell lung cancers?

996
00:58:19.662 --> 00:58:23.462
So this is a whole cleared lung of a genetic model of small cell lung

997
00:58:23.542 --> 00:58:26.842
cancer, where the tumors are labeled in green and the neuronal fibers are labeled

998
00:58:26.882 --> 00:58:30.452
in red. And what you can immediately appreciate is that the tumors are growing

999
00:58:30.452 --> 00:58:34.251
almost exclusively on top of these fibers and that the tumor cells

1000
00:58:34.282 --> 00:58:36.502
themselves are actually quite innervated.

1001
00:58:37.442 --> 00:58:41.202
We can actually quantify this innervation, and indeed, we see by

1002
00:58:41.212 --> 00:58:44.962
branching the number of nerve terminals and as well as

1003
00:58:45.042 --> 00:58:48.962
neurite count, there is a remodeling, even in the lung of these

1004
00:58:49.002 --> 00:58:52.962
nerve fibers, really suggesting that there is neuronal recruitment into

1005
00:58:53.022 --> 00:58:56.802
these nerve fibers. And so we just asked the question, what happens in the lack of

1006
00:58:56.862 --> 00:59:00.222
this nerve fibers? And to ask that question, we performed a

1007
00:59:00.502 --> 00:59:03.562
vagotomy on these mice prior to tumor initiation.

1008
00:59:04.162 --> 00:59:07.582
And to make a long story short, what we found is that in response to this

1009
00:59:07.682 --> 00:59:11.662
denervation, we can dramatically diminish the initiation and growth of

1010
00:59:11.722 --> 00:59:14.902
these tumors. And at the six-month time point, you can see that in the

1011
00:59:14.962 --> 00:59:18.071
sham-manipulated animals, there are huge tumors in

1012
00:59:18.102 --> 00:59:21.672
the entirety of the lung, whereas in the

1013
00:59:21.672 --> 00:59:24.822
denervated mice, we barely see any tumors at all.

1014
00:59:25.642 --> 00:59:29.062
And that certainly translates to a

1015
00:59:29.122 --> 00:59:31.102
massive benefit to survival.

1016
00:59:32.362 --> 00:59:35.972
And so just in my last couple of minutes, I just wanted to tell you about another

1017
00:59:35.982 --> 00:59:39.792
burgeoning story in the lab, really thinking about the brain-body axis of

1018
00:59:39.822 --> 00:59:43.802
these nerve fibers. So if these nerves are being remodeled within

1019
00:59:43.842 --> 00:59:47.582
the lung, and we know that these peripheral nerve circuits are indeed

1020
00:59:47.622 --> 00:59:50.982
communicating with the brain, we wanted to ask the

1021
00:59:51.402 --> 00:59:55.162
question of whether or not there was a broader interaction between the nervous

1022
00:59:55.182 --> 00:59:57.182
system and small cell lung cancer progression.

1023
00:59:58.182 --> 01:00:02.152
So the first thing we did was actually map the innervation from the lung to the

1024
01:00:02.222 --> 01:00:05.802
brain to really understand which of these nerve fibers in the

1025
01:00:05.862 --> 01:00:08.382
lung were actually communicating with the brain.

1026
01:00:08.392 --> 01:00:12.162
The first-order connection actually happens within that nodose ganglia.

1027
01:00:12.172 --> 01:00:15.792
And you can see here that we get a lot of labeling in these tumor-burdened mice in

1028
01:00:15.842 --> 01:00:19.402
those nodose ganglia that then translate into higher order brain

1029
01:00:19.462 --> 01:00:23.362
regions. The first stop is the brain stem, and then we can see multiple different

1030
01:00:23.442 --> 01:00:26.402
regions throughout higher order connections in the brain as well.

1031
01:00:28.122 --> 01:00:31.042
So we wanted to understand whether tumor progression within the lung can actually

1032
01:00:31.122 --> 01:00:35.042
change the activity of any of these actual circuits within the brain.

1033
01:00:35.562 --> 01:00:39.422
So to do that, we did whole-brain clearing and c-Fos labeling to

1034
01:00:39.502 --> 01:00:42.081
