01:01:08.394 --> 01:01:12.024
AMPA-dependent signaling. And I know I'm a little bit short on time here, so I'll

1043
01:01:12.134 --> 01:01:14.094
kind of go through this a little quickly.

1044
01:01:14.574 --> 01:01:17.874
But what we find is that in response to this AMPA

1045
01:01:18.034 --> 01:01:21.574
stimulus in the tumor-bearing mice, we actually see this very clear

1046
01:01:21.714 --> 01:01:25.554
increase in response in the lung tumor-bearing mice, even though we

1047
01:01:25.634 --> 01:01:29.514
actually see no disease burden in the brain itself, which really

1048
01:01:29.554 --> 01:01:33.274
suggests that there's an actual remodeling of these brain circuits

1049
01:01:33.294 --> 01:01:36.514
in response to a

1050
01:01:38.054 --> 01:01:41.934
tumor within the lung. So to understand whether or not these were

1051
01:01:41.954 --> 01:01:45.934
signals that were communicating via the vagus, we again performed this vagotomy

1052
01:01:46.474 --> 01:01:49.714
of these tumor-bearing mice, and again, we're able to see that we can actually

1053
01:01:49.754 --> 01:01:53.714
