1067
01:02:38.774 --> 01:02:41.114
but also cancer neuroscience as a whole.

1068
01:02:41.334 --> 01:02:45.044
We are thinking a lot about these very local interactions of how

1069
01:02:45.074 --> 01:02:48.274
innervation is playing an important role in the context of the local tumor

1070
01:02:48.314 --> 01:02:52.144
microenvironment within the brain, within the lung, and we have a lot of ongoing

1071
01:02:52.214 --> 01:02:56.024
studies there. But I think there's actually a broader view of thinking about this

1072
01:02:56.074 --> 01:02:59.494
as a much more systemic kind of brain-body

1073
01:02:59.594 --> 01:03:03.434
interaction and brain-body disease as a whole that I think is going to have really

1074
01:03:03.474 --> 01:03:04.054
important

1075
01:03:05.234 --> 01:03:08.614
consequences for patients moving forward in terms of their

1076
01:03:08.694 --> 01:03:12.594
overall cognition, their quality of life, their response to therapies,

1077
01:03:12.654 --> 01:03:16.474
et cetera. So, our lab is really focused, again, on understanding the mechanisms

1078
01:03:16.554 --> 01:03:16.674
that

1079
01:03:17.914 --> 01:03:21.894
both drive activity-mediated metastases, but also the role of innervation at

1080
01:03:21.934 --> 01:03:25.634
the primary site, as well as these more systemic interactions at the

1081
01:03:25.694 --> 01:03:29.674
brain-body axes. So, I'm happy to answer questions about any of the

1082
01:03:29.734 --> 01:03:32.934
above. I know we've kind of gone through a broad array of different aspects of

1083
01:03:32.954 --> 01:03:36.204
cancer neuroscience, but I think particularly, especially in the context of small

1084
01:03:36.234 --> 01:03:37.454
cell lung cancer, I think there's

1085
01:03:38.934 --> 01:03:42.354
a lot of work that we can do to move this into the clinic that might be hugely

1086
01:03:42.394 --> 01:03:44.814
